remarks: The predicate " ` B ` is finer than ` A ` ."  (Contributed by Jeff Hankins, 11-Oct-2009.)  (Proof shortened by Mario Carneiro, 11-Sep-2015.)
statement:
isfne.1 $e |- X = U. A $.
isfne.2 $e |- Y = U. B $.
isfne3 $p |- ( B e. C -> ( A Fne B <-> ( X = Y /\ A. x e. A E. y ( y C_ B /\ x = U. y ) ) ) ) $.
